y Universal Form and sta=\r\ny sane or not feel fear and awe. Not one instance. There was in Bengal a gr=\r\neat sadhaka named Swami Nigamananda Saraswati about 150 years ago. He was a=\r\n disciple of the great Aghori Vamakhepa and by Vama&#39;s blessing he had reali=\r\nzed the Goddess Smashan Tara. One day the disciple insisted that he wanted =\r\nto see the Universal form of the Mother Tara. Vama his guru tried to dissua=\r\nde him. But he was adamant and kept asking the form of Ma Tara that he coul=\r\nd see and interact with, to appear in the Universal form. The next thing he=\r\n saw was just a face, whose fierce blood-dripping fangs encompassed the who=\r\nle sky and covered his entire range of vision. Swami Nigamananda fainted im=\r\nmediately. Mind you, he had by then already acquired great proficiency\n in =\r\nworship of Smashan Tara - the very same Devata whom he requested to appear =\r\nbefore him in a Universal form. Later when he came back to senses, he saw V=\r\nama fanning his head and telling him never to ask Her for the Universal for=\r\nm. It simply CANNOT be digested by anyone! \nBasically this \nmean, to me, th=\r\nat our consciousness CANNOT ever comprehend INFINITY as \nit is. It will alw=\r\nays make an approximation for its own good. Moses \ncould not take the raw L=\r\night of God in the burning bush episode on Mt Sinai. Same thing.\n\nSo is it =\r\nthis form of a Devata that we want to see? Is it even possible to see/hear/=\r\ntouch/experience?\n\nMore importantly, what is the difference between these v=\r\narious seeings? Infact, why are they different in the first place?\n\n5. The =\r\nimportant question to ask would be, IMHO, not whether Devatas can be &quot;seen&quot;=\r\n, but what do we, as seekers, expect to happen IF a Devata chooses to manif=\r\nest Himself/Herself on our consciousness? Unless we are very, very, very ex=\r\nceptional, such that a Devata has pre-decided based on certain karmas and p=\r\nromises from past existences to come and intervene in our lifepath - as it =\r\nhappened with Aghori Vimalananda - and pull our strings, chances are that w=\r\ne may not derive much benefit from a casual meeting with a Devata, just lik=\r\ne so many in the Kurukshetra never derived any benefit from meeting Krshna,=\r\n who was a Devata no doubt.\n\nA Devata has various roopas depending on which=\r\n instrument we are using to percieve Him/Her. The sthoola roopa - gross for=\r\nm (rare but not impossible for a Devata). You need the gross phsyical sense=\r\n to experience this. The sukshma roopa where we need subtle senses to perce=\r\nive the Devata. This is what mostly happens with people who &quot;see&quot; Devatas. =\r\nSuch an interaction can very good, to just another day with nothing special=\r\n. It all depends on how much internal preparation has been done by the seek=\r\ner. As an analogy, you can, if lucky, go and meet Barrack Obama say hi and =\r\ncome back. Nothing much happens. Over time you forget it and life goes on. =\r\nOr you can also meet Obama and then maybe impress him so much that he in tu=\r\nrn does something really nice for you which he is well capable of, which su=\r\nstains long and changes your life. \n\nThen there is the causal form and the =\r\ngreater causal form. These are too rare. To have a &quot;Darshan&quot;/experience of =\r\na Devata in these forms, one will have to do solid work of self-transformat=\r\nion. That is detachment, control of internal enemies, etc etc, the standard=\r\n advices which all scriptures and sadgurus tell us. One experience of any D=\r\nevata in the causal form is sufficient to leave a massive impact on a perso=\r\nn&#39;s life for ever. And the greater causal is mostly offlimits for just abou=\r\nt 99.999999% of us. That is the Universal Form. These are similar to experi=\r\nence of the Self or the soul, as enumerated in the Upanishadic literature. =\r\nNothing less.\n\n-Regards\n=C2=A0Rajarshi\n\n\nI have a hundred lives before m